# SPA fallback — every non-file route serves index.html so the client
# router resolves it. index.html is prerendered (scripts/prerender.mjs):
# `/` gets a fast static paint; `/en` has its own prerendered
# en/index.html. Deep routes briefly show the prerendered homepage before
# the router corrects — see PLAN_PRERENDER.md for the clean-shell follow-up.
#
# NOTE: the fallback target MUST be /index.html. Cloudflare Pages rewrites
# a `200` rule that points at any other `.html` asset (e.g. /app.html) into
# a `308` to the extension-stripped URL (/app), which loops the whole site.
/*    /index.html   200
